    {
      "note_no": "9",
      "note": "Sc., \"by showing that you have renounced the practices of the Time of Ignorance\" (Razi). In other words, the pronouncement of zihar is not to be considered a divorce, as was the case in pre-Islamic times, but solely as a reprehensible act which must be atoned for by a sacrifice."
